Four people were reportedly killed while 38 others were injured in an accident involving a car and an articulated vehicle along Oyoâ€“Ogbomoso Road. It was learnt that the driver of the truck veered off the road before the accident that occurred early on Wednesday morning. File photo used to illustrate story. An eyewitness told SaharaReporters that the accident occurred when the driver veered into a ditch and somersaulted. The Oyo State Sector Commander, Winifred U. Chukwurah, confirmed the story to SaharaReporters in Ibadan on Wednesday. SaharaReporters learnt that the remains of the victims had been deposited in a morgue while other victims had been taken to the hospital.